==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Senator
<hw>Sen"a*tor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>senatour</ets>, OF. <ets>senatour</ets>, F.
<ets>s⟦eacute⟧nateur</ets>, fr. L. <ets>senator</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A member of a senate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The duke and <qex>senators</qex> of Venice greet you.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ In the United States, each State sends two senators for
a term of six years to the national Congress.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(O.Eng.Law)</fld> <def>A member of the king's
council; a king's councilor.</def> <rj><au>Burrill.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Senatorial</ent>⟦br⟧
